Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,At Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.16,0:19:53.00,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(279,0)\blur1\fs90\fnCentury\b1\c&H010302&\pos(654,450)}Kamiyama High School
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.17,0:19:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.00,0:19:53.83,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\pos(640,70)\c&HA5BFB6&}Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,According to {\i1}Salute and Solidarity{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.29,0:19:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sekitani Jun, president of the Classics Club, was at the center of the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:19:59.38,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(234,0)\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\c&HA5BFB6&\pos(632,466)}Seki{\c&H5E5C5C&}tani {\c&HA5BFB6&}Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.71,0:20:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the {\i1}Kami High Monthly{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we know that the whole student body was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.39,0:20:05.18,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\pos(640,70)\c&HA5BFB6&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.22,0:20:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would the students have risen up against? The teachers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.85,0:20:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Their reason was, quoting Ibara, that "their autonomy was threatened".
