Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,By "negotiations",
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,do you mean this "culture fair discussion meeting"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Look at it closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.59,0:20:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Each item has either a circle or a square before it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.26,0:20:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.27,0:20:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A square means an event that happens every year, and a circle means this year only!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.52,0:20:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at the other years as well, and that's what I concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now why was there just one "culture fair discussion meeting", 45 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.90,0:21:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Most likely because there was a strong demand for it from the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.12,0:21:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The hint is in {\i1}Hyouka{\i0} itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.70,0:21:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.95,0:21:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"The year that he began as a hero and finished as a legend."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"The culture fair was celebrated for five days as always."{yeah, this was not read in prev ep}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.25,0:21:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The point isn't that it was held, but that it lasted five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that those five days were the fruit of Sekitani Jun's heroic fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.10,0:21:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but maybe the key is this announcement from the principal about the importance of study.
Dialogue: 1,0:21:33.27,0:21:34.60,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs80\fnFranklin Gothic Demi\c&H101065&}5 days
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.27,0:21:34.60,signs,,0,0,0,,{\bord1.5\fs80\fnFranklin Gothic Demi\c&H000000&\3c&H020509&}5 days
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.64,0:21:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The principal had most likely tried to cut the five days of the culture fair short.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.61,0:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why all the students rose up angrily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.19,0:21:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason, the "why".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:44.53,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(317,0)\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\pos(640,70)\c&HA5BFB6&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.45,0:21:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for the way they did it, the "how":
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.74,0:21:48.24,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\pos(640,70)\c&HA5BFB6&}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:51.99,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fnDanger Diabolik\pos(662,666)\c&H1A2361&}Classics Club president Sekitani Jun
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Under the heroic leadership of the Classics Club's president Sekitani Jun,
Dialogue: 1,0:21:51.99,0:21:53.62,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fnDanger Diabolik\c&HEBF3F4&\pos(926,313)}Heroic Leadership
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:53.62,signs,,0,0,0,,{\1a&HFF&\bord1.5\blur0.5\fnDanger Diabolik\c&HEBF3F4&\pos(926,313)\3c&H6C878B&}Heroic Leadership
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.62,0:21:56.46,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fnDanger Diabolik\c&H69A7A6&\pos(589,2)}Daring Activism
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,our daring activism broke the ranks of the spineless authoritarians."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:21:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This leads to the final "what".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.37,0:21:58.17,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs100\fnCentury\b1\pos(640,70)\c&HA5BFB6&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The students used no violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.42,0:22:01.67,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(315,0)\blur1\fs120\fnCentury\b1\c&H7F7E6D&\pos(611,27)}Violence
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.55,0:22:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess they just organized a boycott.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The school had no choice but to negotiate with the students,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.30,0:22:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and they gave up on cutting the culture fair short.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.84,0:22:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But the price they paid was the expulsion of their hero, Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was there a four-month gap between the incident and his expulsion?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:16.64,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fax0.5\fnComic Book\pos(422,24)\c&H478ABC&}Incident: {\c&H6090B3&}June
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:17.10,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fax0.5\fnComic Book\c&H4E4EC8&\pos(294,339)}Expulsion: {\c&H6B9BC4&}October
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If they had expelled him right away, that would have caused even more unrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they waited until after the culture fair, when things had calmed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.74,0:22:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the end of my summary.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.66,0:22:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,45 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.42,0:22:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what happened to my uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.80,0:22:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I could count on you, Oreki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.51,0:22:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That was impressive, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.76,0:22:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It all makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.60,0:22:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki did it again! I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.43,0:22:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.81,0:22:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have any questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.35,0:23:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No issues here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.52,0:23:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to admit it, but he's probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.61,0:23:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll put together an anthology for this year centered around Oreki's theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.20,0:23:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about the details later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This meeting is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.33,0:23:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.04,0:23:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.71,0:23:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.96,0:23:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it was thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.13,0:23:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.26,0:23:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.74,0:23:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.03,0:23:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.62,0:23:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.83,0:24:07.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,300)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.59,0:24:11.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.59,0:24:16.68,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.07,0:24:37.83,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}This sprouting warmth confuses us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.91,0:24:48.75,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Don't you understand this feeling yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.34,0:24:54.84,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Normally such random glances hold no meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.84,0:25:00.18,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,450)\blur2}Isn't it the same when making friends?
